While many brick-and-mortar retail stores have lagged, e-commerce has taken off over the past decade. According to a recent report from the U.S. Census Bureau, U.S. retail e-commerce grew 1.6% between the third and fourth quarters of 2021, and 10.4% from the fourth quarter of the year before.1 One popular type of e-commerce is dropshipping. With a website, e-commerce platform, and wholesale supplier, it’s possible to make money without ever seeing the product in person. Dropshipping companies operate as middlemen and offer features like access to wholesale suppliers, automation, integrations, and data to run your online business. If you’re new to dropshipping, it can be intimidating to try and find the best wholesale suppliers with quality products for your customers. To create our roundup of the best dropshipping companies, we looked at 20 of the most popular options. We compared each company’s history, reputation, pricing, platform, quantity and quality of suppliers, special features, and more. These are the best dropshipping companies for your e-commerce business. The 6 Best Drop Shipping Companies of 2023 Best Overall: Importify Best for Value: Worldwide Brands Best for Newer Businesses: Oberlo Best for Quality Product Suppliers: Spocket Best for Integrations and Automation: Inventory Source Best for Apparel: Printify Best Drop Shipping Companies Expand Best Drop Shipping Companies Our Top Picks Importify Worldwide Brands Oberlo Spocket Inventory Source Printify See More (3) What Is a Dropshipping Company? Is Dropshipping a Good Business? How Much Money Do You Need to Start? What Do Dropshipping Platforms Cost? Methodology Best Overall : Importify Importify Sign Up Now Importify earned our top spot because the company offers the best pricing for unlimited product imports. With plans starting at $14.95 per month, Importify is an affordable option for dropshippers of all levels. The company fully integrates with top e-commerce platforms like Shopify and WooCommerce, and you can import products from hundreds of popular suppliers like AliExpress, Amazon, Etsy, and Walmart. Pros Most affordable pricing Unlimited product imports Semi-automatic order fulfillment through Gold plans Cons Doesn’t offer full automation dropshipping services Only one day for a free trial Customer support via email only Founded in 2016, the growing Givatayim, Illinois-based company offers the best pricing for dropshipping companies. The company also integrates with the best e-commerce platforms and provides access to hundreds of products from top suppliers. Importify isn’t currently accredited by the Better Business Bureau, though. Importify offers three affordable plan options: Basic: $14.95 per monthPremium: $27.95 per monthGold: $37.95 per month These plans allow you to import unlimited products from supported websites. You may easily customize products, set up pricing rules, and change product suppliers. Importify currently only offers a free one-day trial. The Basic plan doesn’t offer access to Amazon. Although the company doesn’t offer full automation services, the Gold plan includes semi-automatic order fulfillment through Amazon, AliExpress, and Dhgate. The company allows you to spy on other Spotify stores to find popular products to sell in your niche. Importify has many reviews in the Shopify app store with 4.5 out of 5 stars.2 Best for Value : Worldwide Brands Worldwide Brands Sign Up Now Worldwide Brands earned a place on our list because the company offers the best value. For $299, you get lifetime access, which is competitive if you’re planning to stay in business for at least a few years. Worldwide Brands also offers one of the best money-back guarantees on the market. If you pay $299 upfront, Worldwide Brands offers a 60-day money-back guarantee, and there is a 30-day money-back guarantee for those who choose the payment plan. Pros 60-day money-back guarantee for $299 plan Access to light bulk wholesalers 16 million certified wholesale products Cons No integration features or automation High upfront fee of $299 Worldwide Brands stands out for value because you get lifetime access to millions of products for $299. If you’re on the fence, the company’s 60-day money-back guarantee makes it worth a try. Founded in 1999, the Maitland, Florida-based company is among the most established dropshipping companies. The company offers dropshipping services with over 16 million products in every category, but unfortunately, you won’t have access to integrations and automations. You will have access to a number of light bulk wholesalers, though, which allow you to buy smaller, more affordable quantities of products while still getting a discount. Worldwide Brands offers two pricing options. You can pay a one-time $299 fee for lifetime access to the company’s wholesale directory, tools for market research, and education. Or you can choose a payment plan: two payments of $110, with $99 down. Best for Newer Businesses : Oberlo Oberlo Sign Up Now Oberlo is the best option for newer businesses because the company offers a generous free plan with access to 500 products, unlimited monthly orders, and the Oberlo Chrome extension. The free plan also includes access to its robust education tools, including a free dropshipping 101 e-course, e-books, and other guides, making it the perfect choice for beginners. Pros Robust free plan option Comprehensive education resources Cons Only integrates with the Shopify platform Smaller selection of suppliers or AliExpress Oberlo is an excellent option for newer dropshippers because of the company’s robust free plan and in-depth educational resources. They offer access to 500 to 30,000 products across all categories, and users have two plan options: Explorer and Boss. The Explorer plan is free and offers access to educational resources, unlimited monthly orders on up to 500 products, and variant mapping. The Boss plan is $29.90 per month includes everything in the Explorer plan, plus the following: Unlimited monthly orders on up to 30,000 productsBulk ordersShipment trackingMultiple staff accountsAffiliate program accessCAPTCHA solver One downside to Oberlo is you only have access to Shopify. Another drawback is you won’t have access to as many suppliers as some competitors. However, you can access products through AliExpress. Best for Quality Product Suppliers : Spocket Spocket Sign Up Now Spocket scored a top ranking because of the company’s commitment to high-quality products. Around 80% of Spocket’s suppliers are in the U.S. or Europe, and all suppliers must go through an in-depth review and onboarding process. Suppliers also must have top-notch products. Other guidelines include no third-party warehouses, discounts on retail prices, and speedy order processing and shipping. Pros In-depth vetting of product suppliers Free 14-day trial with no credit card Branded invoicing Cons Can’t sell products on third-party marketplaces Complaints on Shopify about less competitive product prices Spocket has a strong reputation for access to high-quality product suppliers. Founded in 2017, the company is based in Vancouver, British Columbia. They offer products across multiple industries and fully integrates with Shopify, Wix, WooCommerce, BigCommerce, and AliExpress. The company provides access to distinguished suppliers with up to 10,000 unique products based mostly in the United States and Europe. Spocket offers multiple tiers of pricing for monthly or annual plans. If you pay monthly, there are four tiers: Free: $0 per monthStarter: $29.99 per monthPro: $49.99 per monthEmpire: $99.99 per monthUnicorn: $299.99 per month The less expensive annual plan offers three tiers, with significant discounts provided for paying your year's fees upfront: Pro: $24 discount per monthEmpire: $57 discount per monthUnicorn: $79 discount per month While the free plan only allows a potential seller to browse Sprocket's product offerings and begin planning their dropshipping business, the paid tiers are arranged with set limits of "unique" and "premium" products to sell, plus a host of other useful options. For example, the monthly Starter plan offers access to 25 unique products plus minimal support options, whereas the top-of-the-line Unicorn annual plan allows you to manage sales at a scale with 10,000 unique products, 10,000 premium products, supplier sourcing, bulk checkout, and the ability to request outside products. Spocket currently has many ratings in the Shopify app store, with an overall rating of 4.7 out of 5 stars.3 Best for Integrations and Automation : Inventory Source Inventory Source Sign Up Now Inventory Source earned our pick as best for integrations and automation because the company has over 240 pre-built supplier integrations across various product categories. The company also shines with its automation software. They allow you to sync dropshipping suppliers and product inventory to your e-commerce website, route orders to dropshipping suppliers, and sync-tracking to your store and customers. Pros 240+ pre-built supplier integrations Full automation service Cons Some complaints about software issues on Shopify Inventory Source is a market leader with integrations and automation software. The company was founded in 2002 and is based in Jacksonville, FL. Inventory Source provides services for a range of product categories and integrates with more than 25 e-commerce platforms, including Amazon, eBay, Walmart, Shopify, BigCommerce, and more. The company offers three pricing options: Directory Account: $0 per monthInventory Source: $99 per monthFlxpoint: $599 per month The free Directory Account only offers basic access to the supplier directory by niche, with the ability to preview products and learn how to start your dropshipping business. But if you’re looking for integrations and automations, you will need one of the paid plans. You will have access to the most robust offerings through the company’s Flxpoint plan. Inventory Source currently has many reviews on Shopify’s app store with an overall score of 3.8 out of 5 stars.4 Best for Apparel : Printify Printify Sign Up Now Printify earned a place on the list because of the company’s focus on custom apparel. You may order custom T-shirts, hoodies, sweatshirts, tank tops, sportswear, and shoes in a variety of sizes for men, women, or children. The company also offers all-over-print and eco-friendly apparel options. Pros 800+ custom products for your e-commerce store Mockup generator to design products Access to 80+ printing facilities mostly in the U.S., U.K., and China Cons Shipping rates vary by print provider. Printify is a print-on-demand network with an emphasis on high-quality custom apparel. Headquartered in San Francisco, the company has been in business since 2015. Printify offers dropshipping for 800+ customizable products in five categories: men’s clothing, women’s clothing, children’s clothing, accessories, and home and living. Printify integrates with Shopify, Etsy, WooCommerce, eBay, PrestaShop, BigCommerce, and Wix Stores. You may also access the company’s API for custom solutions. The company offers three pricing tiers: Free: 5 stores per accountPremium: $24.99 per month; 10 stores per accountEnterprise: Custom pricing; unlimited stores per account All three tiers offer unlimited product design and integration with Spotify, Etsy, eBay, and more. Printify offers custom order imports for the Premium and Enterprise levels. It also has many reviews in the Shopify app store with a 4.4 out of 5 stars rating.5 What Is a Dropshipping Company? Dropshipping is an online business where an intermediary sells products they don’t keep in inventory from a wholesale producer to a third party. The third-party company then ships the product directly to the buyer. The intermediary never holds the products, but by purchasing the products at wholesale prices and selling them at retail, the online seller may earn a profit. As you get started with dropshipping, you will need e-commerce software and a website to sell your products. You will also need access to product suppliers through a dropshipping company. Is Dropshipping Still a Good Business? Dropshipping can be a risky business. As a dropshipper, you don’t have control over each step of the sales and delivery process, including the supply chain. You won’t have the chance to inspect every product your customers receive personally, so you will have to rely on wholesale product sellers to ship your products in good condition. You will have to trust the supplier’s authenticity, service, and delivery. Luckily, many dropshipping companies offer access to thousands of vetted product suppliers. This may reduce your chances of having issues with the quality of your products. You may also rest easier knowing a vetted company will provide your customers with quality service and goods. How Much Money Do You Need to Start Dropshipping? While dropshipping companies may claim you don’t need much money to get started, there are some expenses to consider as you’re kicking off your business. You will need a dropshipping company (free to $299) to connect with product suppliers. You will also need a website with e-commerce capabilities where buyers can buy your products. One advantage of dropshipping is you won’t pay for the wholesale products until after the buyer makes a purchase, so you won’t have to pay for inventory. But you will have to spend money marketing your business and products. This may cost as little or as much as you’re willing to invest across multiple channels to spread the word. What Do Dropshipping Platforms Cost? Our research shows the cost of dropshipping companies can vary widely. The pricing may depend on factors like whether you need to access the dropshipping company’s supplier directly, selling products, using data configurations, or accessing automation software. With a basic free plan, you may get access to a platform’s supplier directory and education resources. However, you should expect to pay a monthly fee for additional services. The pricing may range from $14.95 per month for a basic plan to $599 per month for an enterprise plan. Depending on the platform, you may save money by signing up for an annual plan versus paying for the service monthly. You may also have the option to add on extra services for a fee, based on your company’s needs. How We Chose the Best Dropshipping Companies When you’re searching for the best dropshipping company, it may feel like there are endless options to choose from. As e-commerce continues to grow and dropshipping stays affordable, there may be even more companies vying for a slice of entrepreneurs’ business. These companies may offer access to the dropshipping services you need, along with a trusted network of global wholesalers to make your online business possible. To craft our list of the best dropshipping companies, we reviewed 20 of the most popular services. To choose the best for each category, we considered each company’s history, reputation, and what makes the company stand out. To narrow down the list, we compared each company’s integrative platform, pricing, quality and number of suppliers, and options for a risk-free trial. Importify is a dropshipping app that allows you to import products from various suppliers into your Shopify store. It supports multiple platforms such as AliExpress, Amazon, eBay, and more. Here are some of its features:

1. One-click product import: Importify allows you to import products from various suppliers with just one click. You can also edit the product details before importing them into your store.

2. Automated order fulfillment: Importify automates the order fulfillment process by automatically sending orders to your suppliers. This saves you time and effort in fulfilling orders manually.

3. Pricing automation: Importify allows you to set your own pricing rules for your products. You can set a fixed markup or use a formula to calculate the price based on the cost of the product.

4. Product customization: Importify allows you to customize your products by adding your own logo, images, and descriptions.

5. Multiple suppliers: Importify supports multiple suppliers, so you can choose the best supplier for each product.

6. Product reviews: Importify allows you to import product reviews from your suppliers, which can help increase your sales.

7. Customer support: Importify provides customer support through email and live chat.

Overall, Importify is a powerful dropshipping app that can help you streamline your dropshipping business and increase your sales.
